{
  "stem": "8784.1",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My father was a tailor, and this is how he made his living.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He also occasionally was a cantor.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I also-- I don't-- although I don't remember the arrangements, whether he was getting paid for being a cantor or not, but I do remember him praying and conducting services during holidays in, in temples in our neighborhood.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[CLEARS THROAT]",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My family was observant in practices and, and in observing holidays and attending religious services.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was a-- kind of a holy atmosphere in the house when holidays came.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I remember attending temple or shul together with my grandfather.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And this was an extremely pious group of people getting together, and celebrating, and observing holidays.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The Jews living in Poland almost acted like if they lived in Israel, like if they were happy, extremely happy just being able to celebrate holidays, observe holidays.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "There was always plenty of food.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Even if there was a shortage during the week, there was plenty of food supply for holidays.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So it was an extremely joyous occasion.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "It was a happy time during the holidays, Jewish holidays, and observance.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That school I attended for six years in Krakow, in the city of Krakow.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And that meant that I walked from my house in Borek Falecki for about one hour.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It took one hour of walk from my home to the school.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And after attending school in the city of Krakow, I also attended cheder, a religious school in Podgorze, which is the other side of the river of Krakow, on [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And this would have been about the same spot where Oskar Schindler was later on riding a horse and witnessing what was taking place in the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The ghetto could be seen from that spot on [NON-ENGLISH] where I attended the Hebrew school.",
      "word_count": 16
    }
  ],
